00:04:18.460 --> 00:04:24.600
[music]

00:04:24.600 --> 00:04:25.500
Well neat.

00:04:25.500 --> 00:04:27.040
That looks like it might work as a forge.

00:04:27.140 --> 00:04:28.700
&gt;&gt; I think we're missing something.

00:04:29.180 --> 00:04:30.260
That'll work.

00:04:30.260 --> 00:04:32.740
&gt;&gt; So we need the fire
coming out of the torch

00:04:33.260 --> 00:04:35.660
to be going through
the side of the paint can,

00:04:35.660 --> 00:04:36.940
through the kale wool,

00:04:36.940 --> 00:04:40.320
and then blowing fire
right down onto the brick.

00:04:40.520 --> 00:04:42.680
We've got our line,
and we're gonna mark along there,

00:04:42.680 --> 00:04:45.150
and we're going to put
the torch kind of near the front.

00:04:45.150 --> 00:04:47.860
That way if we want to angle it
a little bit more forward, we can,

00:04:47.860 --> 00:04:51.830
and if we want to twist it and angle
a little bit more backwards, we can.

00:04:51.830 --> 00:04:53.400
If we have the torch too far back,

00:04:53.400 --> 00:04:56.620
then we really only have the
option of angling it forward or down.

00:04:57.140 --> 00:04:59.120
Further forward gives
us more space to play with it.

00:04:59.120 --> 00:05:02.640
We are using 5/8 inch
forstner bit to drill our hole.

00:05:02.640 --> 00:05:08.100
[music]

00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:09.100
So at this point,

00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:10.180
we can turn on the fire.

00:05:11.040 --> 00:05:11.980
It's gonna get nice and hot in there

00:05:11.980 --> 00:05:14.780
and we can use
 this for blacksmithing right?

00:05:14.780 --> 00:05:15.740
&gt;&gt; Yes you can.

00:05:15.740 --> 00:05:16.580
&gt;&gt; Wonderful.

00:05:16.580 --> 00:05:19.040
Is there anything else you want
to do with this can before we

00:05:19.050 --> 00:05:20.400
say we're all finished?

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:22.610
&gt;&gt; Well we added these four
bolts on the bottom.

00:05:22.610 --> 00:05:24.259
We want to turn it into a mini foundry.

00:05:24.259 --> 00:05:26.160
We're gonna have to add a second hole.

00:05:26.160 --> 00:05:29.060
&gt;&gt; Once again carefully drilling through
the kaowool without it twisting

00:05:29.060 --> 00:05:31.520
and binding up and without
drilling into my fingers.

00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:34.220
I choose to keep all of
my fingers for now.

00:05:35.080 --> 00:05:36.040
Hopefully, forever.

